org.hypergraphdb.viewer.util

Class ExtFileFilter

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.swing.filechooser.FileFilter
      • org.hypergraphdb.viewer.util.ExtFileFilter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.FilenameFilter

    public class ExtFileFilter
extends javax.swing.filechooser.FileFilter
implements java.io.FilenameFilter
    A convenience implementation of FileFilter that filters out all files except for those type extensions that it knows about. Extensions are of the type ".foo", which is typically found on Windows and Unix boxes, but not on Macinthosh. Case is ignored.
    Version:
    1.0 05/02/03
    Author:
    Larissa Kamenkovich

      • addExtension

        public void addExtension(java.lang.String extension)
        Adds a filetype "dot" extension to filter against. For example: the following code will create a filter that filters out all files except those that end in ".jpg" and ".tif": ExampleFileFilter filter = new ExampleFileFilter(); filter.addExtension("jpg"); filter.addExtension("tif"); Note that the "." before the extension is not needed and will be ignored.
